So data is studies on comparing Nedocromil sodium with placebo for preventing exercise-induced bronchoconstriction

The columns are

  • the author,
  • the year of publication,
  • Ne, the Number of patients (sample size) in the experimental treatment group,
  • Me, the Mean response among the patients in the experimental group,
  • Se, the Standard deviation of the response in the experimental group, and
  • Nc, Mc and Sc the sample size, mean response and standard deviation in the control patients.

                       Nc, Mc, Sc,

3 Continuous response

Two groups

  • experimental
  • control

Usually have for each study \(k\):

\[ \hat\mu_{ek}, s^2_{ek}, n_{ek}, \hat\mu_{ck}, s^2_{ck}, n_{ck} \]

3.1 Mean difference

Same scale

\[ \hat\mu_k = \hat\mu_{ek} - \hat\mu_{ck} \]

meta1 %>% 
  mutate(MD = Me - Mc, 
         lwr = MD - 1.96 * sqrt(Se^2 / Ne + Sc^2 / Nc),
         upr = MD + 1.96 * sqrt(Se^2 / Ne + Sc^2 / Nc))

3.2 Standardised mean difference

Different scales

meta uses Hedges g

\[ \hat{g}_k = (1 - 3/(4n_k-9)) \times \frac{\hat\mu_{ek} - \hat\mu_{ck}} {\sqrt{\frac{(n_{ek} - 1)s^2_{ek} + (n_{ck} - 1)s^2_{ck}}{n_k - 2}}}, \] where

\[ n_k = n_{ek} + n_{ck} \]

Also

\[ var(\hat{g}_k) = \frac{n_k}{n_{ek}n_{ck}} + \frac{\hat{g}^2_{k}}{2(n_k - 3.94)} \]

get_g  <- function(nc, ne, mc, me, sc, se){
  nk  <- nc + ne
  gk  <- (1 - 3 / (4 * nk - 9)) * 
    (me - mc) / sqrt(
      ((ne - 1) * se^2 + (nc - 1) * sc^2) / (nk - 2)
    )
}
get_var_g  <- function(g, ne, nc){
  nk  <- nc + ne
  var_g  <- nk / (ne * nc) + g^2 / (2 * (nk - 3.94))
}
meta2 %>% 
  mutate(
    g = get_g(Nc, Ne, Mc, Me, Sc, Se), 
    vg  = get_var_g(g, Ne, Nc), 
    lwr = g - 1.96 * sqrt(vg),
    upr = g + 1.96 * sqrt(vg)
  )

3.3 Fixed Effect Model

\[ \hat\theta_k = \theta + \sigma_k\epsilon_k, \quad \epsilon_k \stackrel{iid}{\sim}N(0,1). \]

\[ \hat\theta_F = \frac{\sum^K_{k = 1}w_k \hat\theta_k}{ \sum^K_{k = 1}w_k }, \] where

\[ w_k = \frac1{\hat\sigma^2_k} \]

\[ var(\hat\theta_F) = \frac1{\sum^K_{k = 1}w_k} \]

meta1  <- 
  meta1%>% 
  mutate(MD = Me - Mc, 
         v = Se^2 / Ne + Sc^2 / Nc, 
         w = 1 / v)
meta1

3.4 Random Effects Model

\[ \hat\theta_k = \theta + u_k + \sigma_k\epsilon_k, \quad \epsilon_k \stackrel{iid}{\sim}N(0, 1), u_k \stackrel{iid}{\sim}N(0, \tau^2) \]

If study \(k\) is rerun, then new \(u_k\). exchangeability assumption

\[ Q = \sum^K_{k = 1}w_k(\hat\theta_k - \hat\theta_F)^2, w_k = \frac1{\hat\sigma_k^2} \] \(Q\) is homogeneity test stat, heterogeneity statistic.

\[ S = \sum^K_{k = 1}w_k - \frac{\sum^K_{k = 1}w_k^2}{\sum^K_{k = 1}w_k} \]

  1. \(Q < (K - 1)\) set \(\hat\tau^2\) to zero and \(\hat\theta_R\) to \(\hat\theta_F\).
  2. Else \[ \hat\tau^2 = \frac{Q - (K - 1)}{S} \text{ DerSimonian-Larid} \]

\[ \hat\theta_R = \frac{\sum^K_{k = 1}w^*_k \hat\theta_k}{ \sum^K_{k = 1}w^*_k }, \]

\[ var(\hat\theta_R) = \frac1{\sum^K_{k = 1}w^*_k}, \]

where

\[ w^*_k = \frac1{\hat\sigma^2_k + \hat\tau^2} \]

3.5 Prediction

forest(meta1_MA, prediction = TRUE)

4 Binary outcomes

4.1 Setup

df  <- tribble(
  ~group, ~event, ~no_event, ~grp_size, 
  "experiment", "$a_k$", "$b_k$", "$n_{ek} = a_k + b_k$",
  "control", "$c_k$", "$d_k$", "$n_{ck} = c_k + d_k$",
  "", "$a_k + c_k$", "$b_k + d_k$", "$n_k$"
)
df %>% 
  knitr::kable()
group event no_event grp_size
experiment \(a_k\) \(b_k\) \(n_{ek} = a_k + b_k\)
control \(c_k\) \(d_k\) \(n_{ck} = c_k + d_k\)
\(a_k + c_k\) \(b_k + d_k\) \(n_k\)

\[ p_{ek} = a_k / n_{ek}, \quad p_{ck} = c_k / n_{ck} \] ## Odds ratio

\[ \psi_k = \frac{\frac{p_{ek}}{(1 - p_{ek})}} {\frac{p_{ck}}{(1 - p_{ck})}} = \frac{a_kd_k}{b_kc_k} \]
